description.narrative: The project is designed to help the Government of Mauritania to implement its strategy of producing qualified graduates with the skills needed for increased productivity and diversification of its economy. The project aims at:(i)improving the quality of the learning environment and the relevance of courses to the labor market; and (ii)establishing pedagogic, administrative, and financial management systems in the IHEs.

condition.narrative: Annual training program and budget shall be submitted by the Borrower for the Association's approval no later than June 30 everyyear.
Deposit into the Project Account the amount required to cover the Borrower's counterpart contribution for each such followingquarter

Furnish to the Association a financial monitoring report, in form and substance satisfactory to the Association not later than 45days after each subsequent calendar quarter, and shall cover such calendar quarter.

Furnish to the Association as soon as available but in any case not later than six months after the end of each year certifiedcopies of the financial statements and an opinion on such statements by auditors referred to under Art. IV, Sect. 4.01(b) (i)
Prepare Project Implementation Manual acceptable to IDA
Prepare and furnish to the Association not later than six (6) months after the Closing Date or such later date as may be agreedforthis purpose a plan for safeguarding the objectives of the Project

Prepare, through the DPEF, and furnish annually to the CCP and the Association, on or about December 31 of each Fiscal Year, areport integrating the results of the monitoring and evaluation activities performed.
